cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses information theory to establish necessary and sufficient conditions for estimating the principal component using unbounded computational resources. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses several polynomial-time estimation algorithms for tensor PCA and compares their performance. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper analyzes the computational complexity of tensor PCA and discusses the limitations of computationally tractable estimators. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper considers the case in which additional side information is available about the unknown signal and characterizes the amount of side information that allows the iterative algorithms to converge to a good estimate. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses various initialization methods for tensor power iteration and compares their performance.
